"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-29-paris-2024-olympics-super-falcons-solid-vs-spain-must-start-scoring-goals-oshoala\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Super Falcons forward, Asisat Oshoala was satisfied with the team's performance in the 1-0 defeat to Spain but claimed they must work on their finishing.  Alexia Putellas' brilliant late free kick separated both teams in a keenly contested Group C tie at the Stade de la Beaujoire, Nantes on Sunday night.  Captain Rasheedat Ajibade and Chiwendu Ihezuo were guilty of missing good scoring opportunities for the Super Falcons in the game.  Randy Waldrum's also had similar problem in their opening fixture against Brazil which they also lost 1-0.  A disappointed Oshoala said it is important for the Super Falcons to start scoring goals.  \\\"All I can say is I am proud of our performance. I think we played good.  \\\"We played against the world champions and we had our chances, we had opportunities to score Spain, the Bay FC striker said after the game.  \\\"I think the same thing happened to us in the first game. We were not clinical upfront. I think if we start scoring goals we can compete with any team in the world,\\\" he said.  Transfer: Your recruitment team have failed - Gallas slams Chelsea  Kano Pillars get new interim management board  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  Friendly: Cameroon coach gives reason for defeat to Super Falcons  Friendly: Babajide relishes Super Falcons' win over Cameroon  Friendly: Super Falcons floor Cameroon 3-1 in Yaounde  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"